The paper deals with identifying and correcting errors in data produced by information extraction systems, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves machine learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with data cleaning and error correction, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of different models, which could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
